event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "Skip to main content\n\nBEDTIME STORY STUDIO\n\nStoryteller\nSessions\nWorkspace\n\nResume existing stories or open a session workspace when you are ready to continue.\n\nCONNECTION\n\nBackend reachability\nLast checked 9:20 PM.\nOnline\nCheck again\n\nThe app shell is connected to FastAPI through the Vite development proxy.\n\nHello from FastAPI!\n\nSESSION WORKSPACE\n\nAudio Estimate QA\n\nChat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right canvas reserved for structured editing.\n\nCurrent stage\nAudio\nSave status\nSaved Apr 2, 9:17 PM\nSession ID\na059941d-503d-468f-94b5-fca2b62dc4f7\nLive updates\nConnected\n\nSubscribed to session:a059941d-503d-468f-94b5-fca2b62dc4f7. Replaying from sequence 1.\n\nIn progress\nReturn home\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed connected\n\nReady for notes, approvals, and stage edits from the conversation lane.\n\nSystem\nApr 2, 9:17 PM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Audio.\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nReady\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nRegenerate pitches\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nPress Enter to send. Press Shift+Enter for a new line. Try /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nIn progress\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nIn progress\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nConfigure narration and music\n\nThe audio stage will expose narration controls, runtime estimates, and resumable generation progress before the final listenable asset is assembled.\n\nIn progress\nUnlocked\n\nThe route and the durable session stage are aligned. Live editors and job views can mount here later without changing the URL pattern.\n\nAUDIO STAGE\n\nShape the narration pass before the audio render starts.\n\nVoice, delivery, speed, and music stay in one durable plan. The runtime shown here is an estimate, not a guarantee, because the final script and delivery still affect timing.\n\nNarration in planning\nAudio asset pending\n\nVoice\n\nMoonbeam\n\nSoftest and most airy for slower wind-down stories.\n\nMusic\n\nMusic off\n\nThe narration will render dry, with no background bed under the voice.\n\nRuntime estimate\n\nApprox. 15 min\n\nUsually 13-18 min. Approximate preview based on story setup target.\n\nRoute mapping\n\n?stage=audio\n\nRoute preview keeps this stage addressable without mutating the durable current-step pointer.\n\nSettings\n\nKeep the first pass tight: choose the voice, shape the delivery, decide whether music belongs underneath it, and leave any final mix note for the next render.\n\nNarration voice\n\nVoice choice affects the default color and articulation of the narration.\n\nMoonbeam\nHearthside\nStorykeeper\nNarration style\n\nNarration style shapes warmth and softness without changing the story text.\n\nCalm\nHushed\nWarm\nPlayback speed\n0.85x\n\nSpeed nudges the delivery slower or faster without promising an exact final runtime.\n\nNarration volume\n92%\n\nKeep narration comfortably forward even when music is enabled.\n\nBackground music\n\nBackground music stays optional and should stay clearly beneath the spoken voice.\n\nNarration will render without a background bed.\n\nMusic style\n\nChoose the music bed that best matches the current story lane.\n\nLullaby piano\nString drift\nNight ambience\nMusic volume\n24%\n\nKeep the music subordinate enough that consonants and comfort cues stay easy to hear.\n\nMix and delivery note\n\nUse one compact note for anything the sliders cannot express, such as extra softness on dialogue or cleaner chapter pauses.\n\nSave audio settings\nReset\n\nNarration style\n\nCalm\n\nEven pacing with gentle phrasing and clear breath points.\n\nApproximate timing\n\nBased on the story setup target, roughly 1800 words, and a live 0.85x playback preview.\n\nAssumes about 140 words per minute at 0.85x, usually 120-160 words per minute, plus 2 short chapter pauses at roughly 3 seconds each.\n\nExpect a roomy delivery. Actual runtime can still shift once the final narration pass is rendered.\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n8 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Audio with 80% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nGenre pending / Tone pending\n\nThe structured brief, pitch, and beat choices will accumulate here as the session advances.\n\nProduction\n\nAudio\n\n~12 minute runtime / 1800 words / 3 chapters\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"set +H; docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml exec -T browser node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\n\nconst sessionId = 'a059941d-503d-468f-94b5-fca2b62dc4f7';\nconst baseUrl = process.env.TARGET_BASE_URL ?? 'http://frontend:8566';\nconst url = baseUrl + '/sessions/' + sessionId + '?stage=audio';\n\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({\n  headless: true,\n  executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH,\n  args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'],\n});\n\ntry {\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\n  await page.setViewport({ width: 1440, height: 960 });\n  await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: 'networkidle2', timeout: 30000 });\n  await page.waitForFunction(() => document.body?.innerText.includes('Approx. 14 min'), { timeout: 30000 });\n\n  await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const labels = [...document.querySelectorAll('label')];\n    const playbackLabel = labels.find((label) => label.textContent?.includes('Playback speed')) ?? null;\n    if (playbackLabel === null) {\n      throw new Error('Playback speed label not found');\n    }\n\n    const inputId = playbackLabel.getAttribute('for');\n    const input = inputId ? document.getElementById(inputId) : null;\n    if (input instanceof HTMLInputElement === false) {\n      throw new Error('Playback speed range input not found');\n    }\n\n    const descriptor = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(window.HTMLInputElement.prototype, 'value');\n    descriptor?.set?.call(input, '0.85');\n    input.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));\n    input.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));\n  });\n\n  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));\n  const bodyText = await page.evaluate(() => document.body?.innerText || '');\n  console.log(bodyText);\n} finally {\n  await browser.close();\n}\nEOF\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_110", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 208, "prompt_index": 72, "prompt_name": "71 \u2014 Audio Length Estimation Heuristics", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T14:20:33-07:00"}
