{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented audio length estimation end to end and checkpointed the code at `0dbcfd6` (`feat(prompt-71): audio length estimation`). The backend now uses a dedicated estimator with explicit assumptions for bedtime narration pace, chapter-...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_122", "text": "Implemented audio length estimation end to end and checkpointed the code at `0dbcfd6` (`feat(prompt-71): audio length estimation`).\n\nThe backend now uses a dedicated estimator with explicit assumptions for bedtime narration pace, chapter-break pauses, and 15-second rounding. The audio snapshot payload includes those assumption fields, and the audio stage now shows an explicitly approximate runtime that recalculates live when the playback-speed slider changes. The UI also explains whether the estimate is based on accepted draft text or the story-setup target.\n\nVerification:\n- `pytest backend/tests/test_audio_length_estimation_service.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py backend/tests/test_session_hydration_service.py -q` -> `77 passed`\n- `npm --prefix frontend test -- --run AudioSettingsStage.test.tsx audioEstimation.test.ts SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx` -> `37 passed`\n- `npm --prefix frontend run build` -> success\n- `npm --prefix frontend run lint` -> success\n- `ruff check ...` on touched backend files -> success\n- Browser QA against the live Compose app:\n  - baseline screenshot: [prompt-71-audio-estimate-default.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-71-audio-estimate-default.png)\n  - slower-speed screenshot: [prompt-71-audio-estimate-slower.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-71-audio-estimate-slower.png)\n\nRequired reviewer summary written to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/71_audio_length_estimation_heuristics/summary.md).\n\nAssumptions I made: keep the existing `140` wpm bedtime midpoint and `120-160` range, use `3` seconds per chapter break, and round to `15`-second buckets to avoid fake precision.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 228, "prompt_index": 72, "prompt_name": "71 \u2014 Audio Length Estimation Heuristics", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T14:22:42-07:00"}
